#Work area: MarketingExpected travel: 0% - 30%Career status:Employment type: Regular Full TimeCOMPANY DESCRIPTIONSAP is the global market leader for business software and thus contributes a considerable part of the world's economic power grid. At SAP you get your chance to put your ideas into action with maximum impact.The MENA Audience Marketing Manager is responsible for the planning and development of thought leadership / demand / lead generation marketing programs to support SAP's Retail, CP and Telco audience. The role is part of the MENA Marketing Team supporting the MENA MU and Regional view. In line with SAP's CDM (customer driven marketing) collaboration model, the primary function of this role is to own or facilitate the co-development of key programs across regions and EMEA Market Units. This individual will identify synergies within the marketing organization and will focus on delivering innovative, customer centric and multi-channel programs supporting our aggressive pipeline coverage goals, double digit revenue growth and new customer acquisition targets. This individual will also support the development of MU specific plans & programs liaising with key stakeholders including sales, COE and partner organization.EXPECTATIONS AND TASKS-
REPRESENT MENA ON THE GLOBAL &/OR/ EMEA SPRINT TEAM (planning arm within CDM model) to ensure the audience strategy & Bill Of Material embed local requirements.-
OWN THE BUILD OF A SET OF WW &/OR emea PROGRAMS within Sprint Team in close collaboration with the EMEA audience lead, responsible for regional strategy and project management of the Retail, CP and Telco audience. Key areas of responsibilities are as follows:-
Create an integrated program strategy and framework based on available delivery resources.-
Align with key stakeholders to develop the initial program brief.-
Foster collaboration with branding, communications, online, social media, E&C, customer central, Global & EMEA events teams.-
Convert the program brief into the respective campaign architecture including campaign tactics, touches, and channels.-
Focus on pipeline impact and in line with the financial year and quarter allocation.-
Account for all expenditure, and constantly monitor return on investment against forecast and within defined reporting periods.-
BE THE LOCAL COUNTRY MARKETING MANAGER FOR THE ASSIGNED AUDIENCE, which includes build of integrated projects, budget plan, resources and reporting of status and results. Key areas of responsibility as follows:-
Leverage global/regional programs by adapting them for the local market.-
Collaborate with the Demand Centre where central execution eases workload on local resources.-
Manage local stakeholders in the planning, execution and follow up stage.WORK EXPERIENCE-
10 years of relevant experience; global/international experience preferred.-
Experience managing the creation and execution of effective marketing programs, product launches and promotions.-
Relevant software / technology industry knowledge preferred.-
Ability to collaborate and work across virtual teams to achieve combined goals.-
Experience working experience in matrix environment and engaging with global, regional and local sales, marketing and business development teams.EDUCATION AND QUALIFICATION / SKILLS AND COMPETENCIES-
Bachelor's Degree in Business, specialization in Marketing preferred.-
Excellent business-orientation and analytical skills combined with a focus on results.-
Ability to work collaboratively and act as ‘One Team' with other marketing teams and colleagues.-
Excellent organizational skills.-
Accountability for achieving both individual and shared team goals.-
Excellent communication and presentation skills, ability to communicate effectively with peers and management.-
Creative problem-solving abilities.-
The initiative to work independently in a self-directed environment.-
A passion to establish and maintain positive relationships with partners.-
Creativity, enthusiasm and a desire for continuous improvement.
